main event: On November 8, 1956, in Colfax, Iowa, a round, yellow-orange object the size of a dime at arm's length was observed moving upward and to the northwest at a moderate speed for one minute.
interesting points: The observed object was described as round, yellow-orange, and the size of a dime at arm's length.
The object appeared out to a point and was seen moving upward and to the northwest at a moderate speed.
The report indicates that there was no photograph present in the image.
References to the observations of saucer-like objects and unusual configurations were made.
The sighting was visually observed for one minute.
